properties.headline: Dense Fog Advisory issued January 26 at 10:56PM CST until January 27 at 9:00AM CST by NWS Tulsa OK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Visibility one quarter mile or less in dense fog.

* WHERE...In Oklahoma, Cherokee and Adair Counties. In Arkansas,
Carroll, Washington AR, Madison and Franklin Counties.

* WHEN...Until 9 AM CST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Visibilities are expected to be reduced to less than
one quarter mile by the dense fog, creating hazardous driving
conditions.
properties.instruction:
If driving, slow down, use your low beam headlights, and leave
plenty of distance ahead of you.

Be on the lookout for sudden changes in visibility. The patchy
nature of the fog will drop visibilities quickly in a short
distance.  In addition, visibilities may become severely
restricted in valley areas and near rivers, lakes and bridges.

NWSheadline: DENSE FOG ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 AM CST MONDAY
